<p style="text-align:justify;"><span class="AddHand-editors">[W]</span>hen a young Man wishes to take a Wife, he Em<span class="AddHand-editors">[plo]</span>ys his Father, or some other nigh relatives, to go and give the young Woman's father a present of a Gun, or some other valueable article he may have, and to ask for the Daughter<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[I]</span>f the Demand is agreeable, the present is accepted<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[B]</span>ut if they are Sober at the time, the Marriage does not take place till the first Drunken frolic<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[W]</span>hen the Father, or Brother of the yo<span class="AddHand-editors">[u]</span>ng Woman will take her by the Hand and deliver <span class="AddHand-editors">[h]</span>er to the young Man, without any farther Court<span class="AddHand-editors">[ship]</span> or Ceremony, or Even Consulting the young Woman's inclination in the least, and perhaps the young <span class="AddHand-editors">[cou]</span>ple never Spoke to one another before<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[T]</span>he young Man must then go and live with his father in law for a year at least, and all that he hunts, he must <span class="AddHand-editors">[give]</span> to him during that time<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[B]</span>ut the father in law <span class="AddHand-editors">[finds]</span> him in necessaries, and Cloathing, and if he is <span class="AddHand-editors">[a good hunter]</span>, which is the best Qualification he</p>

